{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀπαίρω</b> <br /> (compare ἀπαείρω), <i>future</i> ἀπᾱρῶ: <i>aorist 1</i> ἀπῆρα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 967\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἀπῆρκα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.100, 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.82: _Ionic dialect_ \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>imperfect</i> ἀπαιρέεσκον, variant {ἀπαίρεσκον}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.186\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>lift off,</b> and so, <b>carry off, take away,</b> τὰ ξύλα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage]\">Refs</a>]; <b>remove,</b> τί τινος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1608; τινὰ Σπάρτης [prev. author] “Hel.” 1671; in “IT” 967\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], perhaps <b>get rid of,</b> νικῶν ἀπῆρα φόνια πειρατήρια:—<i>passive</i>, ἀπαίρεται τράπεζα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Achaeus Tragicus 17.5; ἀπό τινος NT.Matt.9.15. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>lead</b> or <b>carry away,</b> τὰς νέας ἀπὸ Σαλαμῖνος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.57; μελάθρων ἀ. πόδα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 774; ἀ. τινὰ ἐκ χθονός [prev. author] “Hel.” 1520. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> elliptically (i.e. ναῦς, στρατόν, etc.), <b>sail away, march away, depart,</b> ἀπαίρειν ἀπὸ Σαλαμῖνος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.60, frequently in 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus, etc.: with _genitive_, ἀπαίρειν χθονός\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>depart from</b> the land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 131; Σπάρτης ἀπῆρας νηΐ Κρησίαν χθόνα [prev. author] “Tr.” 944: with _accusative_ _cognate_, ἀ. πρεσβείαν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>to set out on</b> an embass